Sentencas: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells (MT-SOFCs) are attractive due to their advantages, including high reduction-oxidation (redox) cycling stability and thermal cycling tolerance.
Titulo: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly porous ceramic by low-temperature co-sintering

Sentencas: A method involving sequential dip-coating, leaching, and co-sintering was developed and applied to fabricate inert substrate-supported MT-SOFCs through acid leaching nickel from the conventional Ni-yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) anode.
Titulo: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly porous ceramic by low-temperature co-sintering

Sentencas: A thin current collector was deposited onto the support surface to minimize the current collection losses by collecting current from the entire surface area of the anode.
Titulo: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly porous ceramic by low-temperature co-sintering

Sentencas: A dense electrolyte could be obtained at a co sintering temperature of 1250 degrees C.
Titulo: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly porous ceramic by low-temperature co-sintering

Sentencas: The produced MT-SOFC with the configuration of porous zirconia support/Ni-Scandia-stabilized zirconia (SSZ) anode current collector/Ni-SSZ anode/SSZ electrolyte/strontium-doped lanthanum manganite (LSM)-SSZ cathode/LSM cathode current collector was evaluated by electrochemical characterization tests.
Titulo: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly porous ceramic by low-temperature co-sintering

Sentencas: The inert substrate-supported MT-SOFC exhibited the maximum power densities of 616, 542, 440, and 300 mW cm(-2) at 800, 750, 700, and 650 degrees C, respectively using dry hydrogen and air.
Titulo: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly porous ceramic by low-temperature co-sintering

Sentencas: In addition, the thermal cycling stability of the MT-SOFC was evaluated.
Titulo: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly porous ceramic by low-temperature co-sintering

Sentencas: The cell survived from thermal cycling tests and came out intact after 50 thermal cycles between 700 degrees C and 400 degrees C during an operation time of 50 h.
Titulo: Inert substrate-supported microtubular solid oxide fuel cells based on highly porous ceramic by low-temperature co-sintering
